title: Grateful Dead Live at Mississippi River Festival on 1980-08-16
description: Alabama Getaway-> Promised Land, They Love Each Other, Me & My Uncle-> El Paso, Althea, Looks Like Rain, Tennessee Jed, Easy To Love You, Minglewood Blues, Deal CC Rider-> China Cat Sunflower-> I Know You Rider, Ship of Fools, Estimated Prophet-> He's Gone-> Drums-> The Other One-> Black Peter-> Sugar Magnolia, E:Iko Iko-> E: One More Saturday Night

reviews.review_text:
Skip bad quality first set and go straight to ripping china>rider Skip the first set unless you have a high tolerance for bad sound. The set is great just proceed caveat emptor.
 
Set II is a different show almost with much better low gen quality and alot easier to listen to China>rider which is incredible !! so just go straight to that, CC Rider +++  Estimated is a rowdy outdoors in your face tour de force. Listen to the awesome he's gone which teases a little truckin and then other one  fades to drums and a cool space and explodes out of space in the best other one from 1980 - Better than Gainseville, which until today was my personal favorite of that year. Qulaity dips again with aiko onwards.

This second set kicks ass and is up there with the third night of Nassau, Gainsville, and Penn State, Hartford, and Lewiston as the best shows of the year.

One man gathers . . . To whomever dropped the 50 dollar bill on the ground outside the gate, thanks. And I'm sorry you lost your money ("Here's a fifty-dollar if you dare . . ."). I all I'd had in my pocket that day was the seven bucks for the ticket. But we ended up well-fed after the gig that night, and I'm forever . . . well . . . grateful.
